Lists are a tool to manage a collection of data.
comment.text:
Any information can be stored in a list (including other lists) and they are refered to as items.
Items in a list are ordered and will be returned in the same order or accessed by the same index unless changes are made to alter it.
To create an empty list, use the assignment button and define the value as []
To access an item from a list, use list_name[index_num]. This can also be entered directly into functions.

Objects are a type of entity. They consist of conics, polylines, polymeshes, planes and rays.
comment.text: Objects are formed by a combination of topologies. More information can be found on the page for topo.

comment.shortText: Planes are a type of object.
comment.text:
Planes are imaginary flat surfaces that stretch infinitely along an x and y axis and are defined by two
perpendicular vectors.

comment.shortText: Polylines are a type of object.
comment.text: Polylines are formed from straight line segments joined to form a continuous line.

comment.shortText: Adds a polyline to the model by joining a list of points
comment.text: Creates a straight line segment between every two points and joins them to create a polyline
Creates a closed polyline object by joining the last point to the first point if true

comment.text: Returns null if both points have the same position

comment.text: Parameter to evaluate (0 is the start of the polyline, 1 is the end of the polyline)
The segment of the polyline to evaluate.

comment.shortText: Explodes a polyline into individual segments
comment.text: Each straight line segment in the polyline is returned as a separate polyline object
comment.returns: List of new polylines created from explode

comment.text: Performs transformation on duplicate copy of input polyline if true

comment.shortText: Extends a non-closed polyline by specified distance
comment.text:
Extention is straight and continues in the same direction as the extended segment
Returns null if distance is negative
comment.returns: New polyline object if successful, null if unsuccessful or on error

comment.text: Performs transformation on duplicate copy of input polyline if true

comment.shortText: Extracts a list of segments from a polyline
comment.text:
Specified straight line segments are removed from the polyline and returned as individual polyline objects
The remainder of the polyline is rejoined as much as possible and returned as one polyline if still intact, or multiple polylines if they have been broken up
List returned is in order (from t=0 to t=1 of orginal input pline)
comment.returns: List of new polylines created from extract

comment.text: Index numbers of polyline segments to extract
Performs transformation on duplicate copy of input polyline if true

comment.shortText: Extrudes a polyline according to a specified vector to create a polymesh
comment.text:
Pline is moved by the specified vector and straight line segments are created between the vertices of the input pline and moved pline. The resulting straight line segments and the straight line segments of the input and moved plines are used to define the edges of four-sided polygons. The polygons are joined to create a polymesh
If cap is true, input pline and moved pline are used as edges to create two polygons. The polygones are joined to the polymesh from above.
Vector describing direction and distance of extrusion
Closes polymesh by creating a flat polygon on each end of the extrusion if true
Performs transformation on duplicate copy of input polyline if true

comment.shortText: Checks if the polyline is closed
comment.returns: True if the polyline is closed

comment.shortText: Lofts a list of polylines with the same number of segments to create a polymesh
comment.text:
Straight line segments are created between the vertices of every two input plines. The resulting straight line segments and the straight line segments of the plines are used to define the edges of four-sided polygons. The polygons created from all the plines are joined to create a polymesh
Returns null if polylines do not have the same number of segments
comment.returns: Polymesh created from loft if successful, null if unsuccessful or on error

comment.text: List of polylines to loft (in order)
Closes polymesh by lofting back to first polyline if true
Performs transformation on duplicate copy of input polyline if true

comment.shortText: Sweeps a polyline along a specified polyline to create a polymesh
comment.text: Polyline is used as the cross-section of the polymesh to create
Performs transformation on duplicate copy of input polyline if true

comment.shortText: Polymeshes are a type of object.
comment.text: Polymeshes are formed from flat polygons joined to form a continuous surface.

comment.shortText: Points are a type of entity.
comment.text: Points are defined by a set of x, y and z coordinates.

comment.shortText: Query functions check if an entity fufils certain conditions.
Rays are a type of object.
comment.text: Rays are imaginary lines that stretch infinitely along an axis and are defined by a single vector.

comment.shortText:
Split functions find points of intersection and conics, polylines and polymeshes where two objects
overlap and split the input objects. They return the split segments, arcs or polymeshes in a list of lists.
comment.text:
[0][i] contains the split parts of the first input, where i is the index number of each individual part obtained from the split function.
[1][i] contains the split parts of the second input, if available, where i is the index number of each individual part obtained from the split function.

comment.shortText:
Topology are sub-components within each object that are connected together.
Topology consists of vertices, edges, wires and faces.
